HEADWORD: Phrenograph
<hw>Phre"no*graph</hw> <pr>(fr⟦emac⟧"n⟦osl⟧*gr⟦adot⟧f)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>frh`n</grk>, <grk>freno`s</grk>, the
midriff + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An
instrument for registering the movements of the diaphragm, or midriff,
in respiration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

